      "id": "EV-module_system-001",
      "source_doc": "module_system",
      "category": "WIRING",
      "confidence": "open",
      "question": "How will `tag_atom()` GPE-trace events be ingested in production — beyond the dev-only `console.log`?",
      "best_guess": "A thin telemetry endpoint (e.g. `app/api/atom-trace/route.ts`) that POSTs `{atom_id, tier, virtues, player_id, session_id, ts}` to a Supabase `atom_traces` table. Use cases: most-traversed atoms, choice-distribution per virtue, archetype-skew vs actual play patterns. Volume planning required (one trace per atom per choice per session adds up)."
    },
    "ev:EV-module_system-002": {
      "type": "edge_vector",
      "id": "EV-module_system-002",
      "source_doc": "module_system",
      "category": "INK-AUTHORING",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "question": "What concrete migration path supports a breaking change to the EXTERNAL contract (1.0 → 2.0)?",
      "best_guess": "Loader inspects `module.json.contractVersion` and either (a) refuses to load 1.0 modules (hard-deprecation, fine while install base is Scotch + 1 author) or (b) routes through a 1.0-shim that re-binds renamed/removed EXTERNALs to no-ops with a deprecation warning. Cost of breaking 1.0 is currently zero — no community modules exist — but Steam Workshop / Itch.io uploads make this load-bearing."
    },
